data.description: This charming 5 bedroom 3 &1/2 bath home has just had a full bathroom and two bedrooms added on the 1st floor. The first bedroom has a cozy fireplace centered on one wall and a window on another wall. Just outside this bedroom door are both a full bath and a 1/2 bath; which makes this room perfect for seniors, a college student and/or as a guest bedroom. The second bedroom downstairs can be used as a bedroom, den, or whatever suits your fancy. The architecture used to add these two bedrooms into the downstairs area worked out perfectly in that they fit naturally and they do not interrupt with the flow of the home. This home sets on a .35 acre of land that has two tuff sheds and one wooden shed that looks like a dollhouse. On the West side of the home is an expansive 13 ft by 65 ft driveway for that extra large motorhome, boat, and /or as many cars that will fit. There is also a large backyard patio area. A past home owner was a cement contractor and he did an awesome job on this yard. Even with all this cement work the back yard is still big enough for anything you can imagine. How about a pool or even an ADU or both? A brand new central air conditioner was just installed last year. The entire home has new vinyl floor planks that even go up the stairs with awesome bullnose edging.
